ana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#444444>6:41:59 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Formal Invitation</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Well,  as many of you know already..some of us that wanted to take a break from D2 have started playing Everquest.  There are about 10 of us that play on a very active basis. Now thats not alot of people. With the differences in time zones and life schedules, it is difficult to get more then 6 of us playing at one time. <br>
<br>
What I would like to do is formally invite any and all KOB members to come and join the KOB EQ community.<br>
If you have a friend that play EQ..maybe you can drop by their place sometime and see what its like. If not..please go to the EQ links page and read up on EQ.  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.graffe.com/links/newsinfolinks.htm">www.graffe.com/links/newsinfolinks.htm</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
EQ is a community based game and best played in groups and we have the best group of people in the gaming world here in the KOB.  You can play this game alone...but it is ALOT more fun with friends. Dont take anyones word for how the game is...try it for yourself...I think it was worth it for me.<br>
<br>
And for DaOzman's sake.....YOU WILL CONFORM!!!!!!!! LOOK INTO THE TUNNEL...DEEP INTO THE TUNNEL!!!!<br>
<br>
Thanks and take care,<br>
<br>
Brostin+KOB+</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#333333><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bknightsofbnet.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=tekwolf>Tekwolf</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.geocities.com/TimesSquare/Dragon/9007/peon2.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#444444>10/4/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#444444>7:38:05 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Formal Invitation</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Verant's actions toward their playerbase are blatantly oppressive and tyrannical.  Still, EQ can be fun, if you don't get <A HREF="http://www.lumthemad.net/news/970718644,57681,.shtml">banned for writing a grapic RPing story</A> or <A HREF="http://www.lumthemad.net/news/970246505,87909,.shtml">banned for trying to improve the clunky interface</a>.  Plus, ya have to pay.  ;(<br>
<br>
Don't let me deter you, though.  EQ can be fun, if played with the right attitude...can be very, very frustrating, however.</font><P>Lord Tiganos<br>
B.net: Tekwolf<br><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#222222><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bknightsofbnet.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=natelkob>NaTel KoB</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>The All Powerful</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#444444>10/5/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#444444>5:01:23 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Formal Invitation</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Tek,<br>
<br>
I can't speak about any tyrannical oppression.  I don't try to change interfaces and such...I just want an immersive game, and EQ definitely has it.  The biggest frustration for me is that it takes a long time to level.  I have played almost a month and am only level 10.  I can get to level 25 in a long weekend of D2.<br>
<br>
It just boiled down to the fact that I wasnt having as much fun with D2 as I did with the original Diablo.  That was hard to say because I played the original Diablo/Hellfire for well over a year with just a couple of breaks.<br>
<br>
We can try to fight it, but we cant resist for long...the FUTURE in RPG is multi-user persistent online RPG's (e.g. UO, EQ, Asheron's Call, etc.).  They will get better and better, and better!  They allow for thousands of people to interact in the same game.  Let's face it people...how cool would it be if we could get 40-50 KoB members in one game area?!  Break up into hunting parties and just rampage the earth.  We are limited in Diablo to small parties, and although it is fun, you dont really ever feel like you do in a persistent world RPG.<br>
<br>
We can have people that create blasksmiths, jewelers, tailors, fletcher's, baker's each helping to create items for the rest of the members.<br>
<br>
Anyway, I am not done with Diablo 2, but I am very glad I tried EQ.  The main point Brostin makes is valid.  The most important thing is GROUP fun!<br>
<br>
See you later comrades!<br>
<br>
NaTel</font><P><img src=http://www.geocities.com/antimache_kob/pics/natel.gif><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#333333><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ucptndragonkob.showPublicProfile?language=EN>CptnDragon  KoB</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>The All Powerful</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#444444>10/6/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#444444>12:43:27 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Formal Invitation</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I couldn't have put it better!  (well maybe but im not going to try for everyones sake)  Its not repetitive, the more people the more differant it can be!  I have seen no 2 people yet that are even close to alike!  Its so big with so many people you get lost, all the time!  Its a game that thrives on Player interaction, just amazing!  (i almost sound like a game critic!)</font><P><img src="http://home.socal.rr.com/oznsoo/images/capn2.jpg">

